HEADWORD: Soya
<hw>Soy"a</hw></mhw>
<pr>(soi"⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Chinese
<ets>sh⟦omac⟧y⟦umac⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A Chinese and
Japanese liquid sauce for fish, etc., made by subjecting boiled beans
(esp. soybeans), or beans and meal, to long fermentation and then long
digestion in salt and water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

